FBIS4-10997 "drlat077_a_94013" FBIS-LAT-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Peruvian Minister on Purchasing Pharmaceuticals Peruvian Minister on Purchasing Pharmaceuticals FL2004140794 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in Spanish 0000 GMT 20 Apr 94 FL2004140794 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks Spanish BFN [Text] On 19 April, Peruvian Public Health Minister Jaime Freundt-Thurne announced that the Peruvian Government is studying the possibility of broadening and strengthening commercial ties with Cuba by purchasing Cuban-made medicines. Freundt-Thurne stated that both the Cuban health system and pharmaceutical industry were excellent despite the difficulties Cuba is currently experiencing. Freundt-Thurne, who is visiting Cuba by invitation of Cuban Public Health Minister Julio Teja, told Teja that Peru wants to broaden ties with Cuba.
